Radarr is an independent fork of Sonarr reworked for automatically downloading movies via Usenet and BitTorrent. The project was inspired by other Usenet/BitTorrent movie downloaders such as CouchPotato. It can monitor multiple RSS
feeds for new episodes of your favorite movies and will grab, sort and rename them. It can also be configured to automatically upgrade the quality of files already downloaded when a better quality format becomes available.

It is not recommended to run Radarr as root. The default user/group is
'radarr'.
You can either create this user like this:

    # groupadd radarr
    # useradd -d /var/lib/radarr -s /bin/false -g radarr radarr 

Or you can pass a different user/group if you prefer:

    # RUN_USER=foo RUN_GROUP=bar ./$PRGNAM.SlackBuild

You can have Radarr start/stop automatically at boot/shutdown. In
/etc/rc.d/rc.local add:

    # Start Radarr at boot
    if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.radarr ]; then
      /etc/rc.d/rc.radarr start
    if

And in /etc/rc.d/rc.local_shutdown add:

    # Stop Radarr at shutdown
    if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.radarr ]; then
      /etc/rc.d/rc.radarr stop
    if

After installing visit http://localhost:7878 to configure Radarr.
